io.discloader.discloader.entity.util

Interface ISnowflake

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IAuditLogEntry, IChannel, IChannelCategory, IEmoji, IGroupChannel, IGuild, IGuildChannel, IGuildEmoji, IGuildMember, IGuildTextChannel, IGuildVoiceChannel, IIntegration, IInviteChannel, IInviteGuild, IMessage, IMessageAttachment, IOverwrite, IPrivateChannel, IRole, ITextChannel, IUser, IUserConnection, IVoiceChannel, IWebhook
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AuditLogEntry, Channel, ChannelCategory, DLUser, Emoji, GroupChannel, Guild, GuildChannel, GuildEmoji, GuildMember, InviteChannel, InviteGuild, Message, Overwrite, PrivateChannel, Role, TextChannel, User, UserConnection, VoiceChannel, Webhook
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ISnowflake
    Discord utilizes Twitter's snowflake format for uniquely identifiable descriptors (ID's). These ID's are up to 64bits in size (e.g. a uint64) and therefore are always returned as strings in the API to prevent integer overflows in some languages. Snowflake ID's are guaranteed to be unique across all of Discord, except in some unique scenarios in which child objects share their parents ID.

    All objects with IDs must implement this interface
    Objects that have Snowflake IDs.
    • channels
    • messages
    • guild emojis
    • guilds
    • users
    • message attachments
    Author:
    Perry Berman
